# Shared action (P#17): creates a product under the calling test's own auth (its session headers
# or manually-set headers both apply, since the action's steps splice into the same test), gives
# back its id. Actions get their own scope, no closures over the caller (SPEC §8) — `categoryId`
# is an explicit parameter, not implicit scope.

action create product(name, price, stock, categoryId)
  api POST /products body { name: {name}, price: {price}, stock: {stock}, categoryId: {categoryId} }
  expect status equals 201
  capture body.id as id
  give id
